<!-- PAGE 6: ABSTRACT -->
<div class="pb"></div>
<h1 class="ct">Abstract</h1>
<p>SHREE Collective is a premium, full-stack luxury Indian couture e-commerce platform designed to digitize the high-fashion ethnic wear market. The platform bridges traditional craftsmanship&mdash;such as zardozi embroidery, gota patti work, and heritage Banarasi silks&mdash;with a cutting-edge, modern web experience.</p>
<p>Built using a decoupled three-tier architecture, the system leverages <strong>React 19</strong> with <strong>Vite</strong> for a highly responsive Single Page Application (SPA) frontend, <strong>Node.js</strong> with <strong>Express.js</strong> for a robust RESTful API backend, and <strong>MongoDB Atlas</strong> for flexible, schema-driven NoSQL data storage via the Mongoose ODM.</p>
<p>Key features include a comprehensive product catalog with category-based filtering, a secure dual-mode authentication system (email/password with bcrypt hashing and Google OAuth via Firebase), a real-time cart management system powered by React Context API, a complete order lifecycle with status tracking, and an administrative dashboard for catalog and order management.</p>
<p>Performance optimizations&mdash;including IntersectionObserver-based lazy loading for media assets and CSS skeleton loaders&mdash;ensure a seamless, high-performance user experience with sub-second initial load times and zero cumulative layout shift. The platform achieves 90+ Lighthouse performance scores across all audit categories.</p>
<p><strong>Keywords:</strong> MERN Stack, E-Commerce, React, Node.js, MongoDB, JWT Authentication, REST API, Firebase OAuth, Luxury Fashion, Single Page Application.</p>

