<!-- CHAPTER 1: INTRODUCTION -->
<div class="pb"></div>
<h1 class="ct">Chapter 1<br>Introduction</h1>

<h2>1.1 Overview</h2>
<p>The global e-commerce market has witnessed exponential growth, with the Indian fashion segment alone projected to reach $35 billion by 2027. However, the luxury ethnic wear niche remains significantly underserved in the digital space. Most existing platforms either cater to mass-market consumers or repurpose generic Shopify-based templates that fail to convey the premium brand narrative essential for high-value couture.</p>
<p>SHREE Collective addresses this gap by providing a purpose-built, full-stack e-commerce platform that combines the visual richness and immersive storytelling expected by luxury consumers with the technical robustness of a modern MERN-stack application. The platform showcases traditional Indian craftsmanship&mdash;including zardozi embroidery, gota patti work, chikankari, and heritage Banarasi weaves&mdash;through a carefully curated digital experience.</p>

<h2>1.2 Identification of Client &amp; Need</h2>
<p>The platform serves two primary user personas:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Collectors (End Consumers):</strong> Affluent individuals seeking authentic, handcrafted Indian ethnic wear (lehengas, sarees, sherwanis, anarkalis) with a seamless online purchasing experience that mirrors the exclusivity of in-store luxury shopping.</li>
<li><strong>Administrators (Boutique Owners):</strong> Business operators requiring a streamlined dashboard to manage product catalogs, track orders, and handle customer inquiries without extensive technical knowledge.</li>
</ul>

<h2>1.3 Problem Identification</h2>
<p>Through analysis of existing Indian ethnic wear e-commerce platforms, the following problems were identified:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Poor Performance:</strong> Heavy, unoptimized image assets cause slow initial page loads (often exceeding 5 seconds), leading to high bounce rates.</li>
<li><strong>Inadequate Visual Fidelity:</strong> Generic templates with cluttered interfaces fail to convey the premium narrative of luxury products.</li>
<li><strong>Monolithic Architecture:</strong> Tightly coupled frontend and backend code limits scalability and independent deployment.</li>
<li><strong>Weak Security:</strong> Many platforms store passwords in plaintext or use deprecated hashing algorithms, exposing user data to breaches.</li>
</ol>

<h2>1.4 Objectives</h2>
<p>The primary objectives of this project are:</p>
<ol>
<li>Design and implement a visually premium, responsive SPA frontend using React 19.</li>
<li>Develop a secure, scalable RESTful API backend with Node.js and Express.js.</li>
<li>Implement robust authentication supporting both email/password and Google OAuth.</li>
<li>Design a flexible NoSQL database schema capable of handling heterogeneous product attributes.</li>
<li>Achieve 90+ Lighthouse performance scores through lazy loading and skeleton UI patterns.</li>
</ol>

<h2>1.5 Task Identification &amp; Timeline</h2>
<p class="c"><strong>Table 1.1: Project Development Timeline</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Phase</th><th>Task Description</th><th>Team Member</th><th>Duration</th></tr>
