<!-- APPENDIX -->
<div class="pb"></div>
<h1 class="ct">Appendix</h1>

<h2>A. User Manual</h2>
<p><strong>Step 1: Prerequisites</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Node.js v18+ and npm v9+ installed on the system.</li>
<li>A MongoDB Atlas account with a configured cluster.</li>
<li>A Cloudinary account for image hosting.</li>
<li>A Firebase project with Authentication enabled.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Step 2: Installation</strong></p>
<pre>
git clone https://github.com/Goldypahal/SHREE.git
cd SHREE
npm install
cd server &amp;&amp; npm install
</pre>

<p><strong>Step 3: Environment Configuration</strong></p>
<p>Create a <code>.env</code> file in the <code>server/</code> directory with the following variables:</p>
<pre>
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://&lt;user&gt;:&lt;pass&gt;@cluster.mongodb.net/shree
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key
PORT=5000
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173
</pre>

<p><strong>Step 4: Database Seeding</strong></p>
<pre>
cd server
node seed.js
</pre>

<p><strong>Step 5: Running the Application</strong></p>
<pre>
# Terminal 1 - Backend
cd server &amp;&amp; npm start

# Terminal 2 - Frontend
npm run dev
</pre>
<p>Access the application at <code>http://localhost:5173</code>.</p>

<h2>B. Project Repository</h2>
<p>The complete source code is publicly available at:<br>
<strong>https://github.com/Goldypahal/SHREE</strong></p>

